# FraudShield AI — Demo Script (5 min)

> **Don't memorize.** Just follow the clicks and talk naturally.

---

## 🎬 Opening (20 sec)

**Say:**
> "FraudShield AI — real-time fraud detection trained on 590K real bank transactions. It scores every transaction in under 50ms, explains why, and tells the bank what to do — approve, PIN, biometric, or block."

---

## 1️⃣ Command Center (50 sec)

**On screen:** Already here. Scroll slowly.

**Say while pointing:**
> "4 KPIs at top — 0.9776 AUC, 0.76 F1, 83% precision with only 5 false positives per thousand, and 25 detection layers all live."

**Point to Architecture Pipeline:**
> "5-stage pipeline: raw data → 25 feature layers → 8-model ensemble → conformal calibration → 4-tier routing."

**Point to Model Leaderboard:**
> "7 models ranked by AUC. XGBoost leads at 0.9776, stacking ensemble at 0.9763."

**Point to Detection Layers grid (quickly):**
> "25 layers — velocity, graph analysis, behavioral DNA, SIM swap, mule network, and more."

---

## 2️⃣ Risk Analyzer (50 sec) ⭐ KEY DEMO

**Click:** `Risk Analyzer`

**Do quickly:**
1. Amount → `5000`, Category → `Digital Goods`, Hour → `3`, Velocity → `15`
2. Check ✅ New Device
3. Click **RUN RISK SCORE**

**Say when gauge shows:**
> "Score ~75, RED zone — system blocks this. On the right: explainable risk factors — SHAP tells us exactly WHY. High amount, 3 AM, new device, high velocity. Every decision is auditable for regulators."

---

## 3️⃣ Model Lab (30 sec)

**Click:** `Model Lab`

**Say (don't wait, talk while it loads):**
> "Radar chart comparing all models on 5 metrics — AUC, precision, recall, F1, specificity. Below that, interactive ROC curves. XGBoost and Stacking dominate but even our weakest model hits 0.72."

---

## 4️⃣ Fraud Network (25 sec)

**Click:** `Fraud Network`

**Say:**
> "Graph-based detection using NetworkX. Each dot is a transaction — connected if they share cards, devices, or addresses. Green dots spread naturally. Red clusters are fraud rings — detected automatically using Louvain community detection."

---

## 5️⃣ Analytics (20 sec)

**Click:** `Analytics` — scroll quickly

**Say:**
> "Score distribution: most transactions land 15-35, safe zone. Only 1.4% flagged high-risk. Routing donut shows 55% auto-approved, 41% need PIN, 2% biometric, 1.3% blocked — legitimate customers aren't disrupted."

---

## 6️⃣ Speed Round — Remaining Pages (40 sec)

**Click through fast, one sentence each:**

**`Flagged Queue`:**
> "Operations team sees all flagged transactions with risk scores and categories — RED block, ORANGE biometric."

**`ROI Calculator`:**
> "Plug in your bank's numbers — it calculates annual savings. Shows before vs after FraudShield deployment."

**`Robustness`:**
> "We tested 5 adversarial attacks — Gaussian noise, feature zeroing, boundary probing — all passed. AUC stays above 0.92 under attack."

**`Threshold Tuner`:**
> "Cost-sensitive threshold optimization. FN costs ₹850, FP costs ₹25with configurable rates — finds the sweet spot."

**`Risk Heatmap`:**
> "Amount vs time-of-day risk density. Hot spots at high amounts + late night — exactly where fraud concentrates."

---

## 7️⃣ Live Stream (15 sec)

**Click:** `Live Stream` → Click **START STREAM**

**Say (while transactions flow):**
> "Real-time WebSocket feed — transactions scored live with color-coded risk. This connects to our FastAPI backend which also auto-generates PDF audit reports."

---

## 🏁 Closing (10 sec)

**Say:**
> "End-to-end system: 25 feature layers, 8-model ensemble, 0.9776 AUC, explainable decisions, graph fraud detection, and production-ready with Docker, API, and live deployment. Thank you."

