## ❓ Judge Q&A Cheat Sheet

| Question | Answer |
|----------|--------|
| What dataset? | IEEE-CIS Kaggle — 590K real bank transactions, 434 features |
| Why ensemble? | Different models catch different patterns; stacking combines strengths |
| Class imbalance? | 3.5% fraud. Stratified k-fold, class weights, threshold optimization |
| Conformal prediction? | Wraps any model to guarantee 95% prediction coverage |
| Inference speed? | Under 50ms via FastAPI |
| Adversarial robustness? | 5 attack types tested, all passed, AUC stays >0.92 |
| PDF reports? | Auto-generated after pipeline run — includes metrics, charts, recommendations |
| How deployed? | Streamlit Cloud (dashboard) + Docker (API) + Render-ready |
| Mobile app? | PWA with transaction scanning, WebSocket alerts, vibration feedback |
| Why 25 layers? | Each captures a different fraud signal — more diversity = better ensemble |
| Train/test leakage? | Adversarial validation AUC = 0.5004 — confirmed no leakage |


> **Tip:** Don't memorize. Just follow the flow and talk naturally. Each section tells you **what to click** and **what to say**.

