## 🎬 Opening (30 sec)

**Say:**
> "This is FraudShield AI — a real-time fraud detection system. We trained it on 590,000 real bank transactions from the IEEE-CIS dataset. It scores every transaction in under 50 milliseconds and tells the bank exactly what to do — approve, ask for PIN, request biometric, or block."

**Click:** You should already be on **Command Center**

---

## 1️⃣ Command Center (60 sec)

**On screen:** The main dashboard with KPIs, pipeline, and leaderboard

**Say while scrolling down slowly:**
> "The system runs on a 5-stage pipeline:
> - First, we ingest 590K transactions with 434 raw features
> - Then we engineer **25 detection layers** — things like velocity patterns, behavioral DNA, graph analysis, SIM swap detection
> - These feed into an **8-model ensemble** — XGBoost, LightGBM, CatBoost, Random Forest, MLP, Isolation Forest, TabNet, and an Autoencoder
> - We calibrate using **conformal prediction** — so we can guarantee 95% coverage
> - Finally, a 4-tier risk routing decides: approve, PIN, biometric, or block"

**Point to Model Leaderboard:**
> "Our best model — XGBoost — hits **0.9776 AUC**. The stacking ensemble is close at 0.9763."

**Point to Detection Layers grid:**
> "These are all 25 feature layers. Each one captures a different fraud signal."

---

## 2️⃣ Risk Analyzer (60 sec)

**Click:** `Risk Analyzer` in sidebar

**Say:**
> "This is the interactive scoring engine. Let me show you a suspicious transaction."

**Do this:**
1. Set **Amount** to `5000`
2. Set **Category** to `W — Digital Goods`
3. Set **Hour** to `3` (3 AM)
4. Set **Velocity** to `15` (15 txns in 24h)
5. Check ✅ **New/Unknown Device**
6. Click **RUN RISK SCORE**

**Say when results appear:**
> "Score is around 75 — that's in the RED zone. The system would block this transaction. 
> On the right you can see the **explainable risk factors** — it's flagging the high amount, the 3 AM timing, the new device, and the high velocity. 
> This is powered by SHAP — so every decision is explainable to regulators."

---

## 3️⃣ Model Lab (45 sec)

**Click:** `Model Lab` in sidebar

**Say:**
> "Here we can compare all 7 models head-to-head."

**Point to Radar Chart:**
> "The radar chart shows 5 metrics — AUC, Precision, Recall, F1, and Specificity. XGBoost and the Stacking Ensemble dominate across all dimensions."

**Point to ROC Curves:**
> "And these are the ROC curves. You can see even our worst model — Isolation Forest — still achieves 0.72 AUC. The top models are all above 0.96."

---

## 4️⃣ Fraud Network (45 sec)

**Click:** `Fraud Network` in sidebar

**Say:**
> "This is our graph-based fraud detection. Each dot is a transaction. We connect them if they share cards, devices, email domains, or addresses."

**Point to clusters:**
> "Green dots are legitimate — they're spread out, no shared infrastructure. 
> But see these **red and orange clusters**? Those are fraud rings — multiple transactions sharing the same card or device. 
> We use **Louvain community detection** from NetworkX to automatically find these clusters."

**Point to stats below:**
> "Out of 200 sampled transactions, only 3 are high-risk — but they cluster together, which is exactly what real fraud rings look like."

---

## 5️⃣ Analytics (45 sec)

**Click:** `Analytics` in sidebar

**Say:**
> "The analytics page shows the full score distribution across 10,000 transactions."

**Point to histogram:**
> "Most transactions score between 15-35 — that's the safe zone. The red tail on the right is the ~1.4% flagged as high-risk."

**Point to donut chart:**
> "Our 4-tier routing: 55% get auto-approved, 41% need just a PIN, about 2% need biometric verification, and only 1.3% get blocked. So we're not blocking legitimate customers."

---

## 🏁 Closing (30 sec)

**Say:**
> "To summarize:
> - **0.9776 AUC** on real bank data
> - **25 feature layers** catching different fraud patterns
> - **8 models** in an ensemble with conformal prediction
> - **Explainable** decisions using SHAP
