## ❓ Common Judge Questions

| Question | Quick Answer |
|----------|-------------|
| "What dataset?" | IEEE-CIS from Kaggle — 590K real bank transactions, 434 features |
| "Why not just one model?" | Ensemble catches different patterns; stacking combines their strengths |
| "How do you handle class imbalance?" | 3.5% fraud rate. We use stratified k-fold, class weights, and threshold optimization |
| "What's conformal prediction?" | It wraps any model to give uncertainty guarantees — we guarantee 95% coverage |
| "How fast is inference?" | Under 50ms per transaction via FastAPI |
| "What about adversarial attacks?" | We tested 5 attack types — all passed. AUC stays above 0.92 under perturbation |
| "Why 25 feature layers?" | Each captures a different fraud signal — velocity, graph, behavioral. More diverse features = better ensemble |
| "How is it deployed?" | Streamlit Cloud for dashboard, Docker for API, also deployable to Render |
